#d
# consider only Billoweg stop
 BL <- sqldf("select * from FS_04 where short_name_stop_after like '%Billoweg%'  or short_name_stop_from like '%Billoweg%' ")

#create new variable that specidied hour for target departure times
BL_01 <- BL %>% mutate(Target_from_hour = round(Target_asof_from/3600, 0), Target_after_hour = round(Target_asof_after/3600, 0) )

#Only consider trips between 9:00 and 15:00
BL_02 <- BL_01 %>%  filter(Target_from_hour %in% (9:15) & Target_after_hour %in% (9:15) )

#Direction 1
BL_03 <- BL_02 %>% filter(guideway_typ == 1)
BL_04 <- BL_03 %>% select(Short_name_stop_from, Short_name_stop_after, Target_from_hour, Target_after_hour)
BL_05 <- unique(BL_04)

# t-test for one trip
BL_06 <-sqldf("select * from BL_05 where Short_name_stop_from like '%Brunaustrasse%' or  Short_name_stop_after like '%Brunaustrasse%'")
t.test(BL_06$Target_from_hour, BL_06$Target_after_hour)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  BL_06$Target_from_hour and BL_06$Target_after_hour
## t = 0, df = 26, p-value = 1
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -1.61249  1.61249
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##        12        12
FS_05 <- FS_04 %>% mutate(Target_from_hour = round(Target_asof_from/3600, 0), Target_after_hour = round(Target_asof_after/3600, 0) )
t.test(FS_05$Target_from_hour, FS_05$Target_after_hour)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  FS_05$Target_from_hour and FS_05$Target_after_hour
## t = -0.31044, df = 331530, p-value = 0.7562
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.04323826  0.03141422
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  14.01487  14.02078

The only problem in using all the trips is you cannot make sense of which trip to and fro has caused a delay if there is a significant difference in mean.

The p value proves that there is no statistically significant difference between the Target_from_hour and Target_after_hour.

  1. In the t test in d) we are using data of one trip per hour in each direction and since there are no differences it implies that it is not subsequently adding any delays.
